'''Josh Fadem''' (born July 19, 1980) is an American actor, writer, and comedian.  He is known for playing the camera guy, Joey Dixon on the [[AMC (TV channel)|AMC]] series ''[[Better Call Saul]]'' and [[Liz Lemon]]'s agent Simon Barrons on the [[NBC]] series ''[[30 Rock]]''.  He has also appeared on ‘’[[Twin Peaks, the Return]]’’ as Phil Bisby, ''[[Key & Peele]]'', ''[[It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia]]'', ''[[The Whitest Kids U' Know]]'', and ''[[Comedy Bang! Bang!]]''. He starred in the Misfits and Monsters episode "Patsy". Fadem was born and raised in [[Tulsa, Oklahoma]] where he attended Booker T. Washington High School, but has lived and worked in [[Los Angeles]] since 2000.<ref>{{cite web |last=Peyser |first=Eve |title=Comedian Josh Fadem on the art of acting dumb |work=[[The Daily Dot]] |date=September 26, 2015 |url=http://www.dailydot.com/entertainment/josh-fadem-interview/ |accessdate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Smith |first=Michael |title=Josh Fadem returns home for 'Tulsans in Cinema' screening, discussion |work=[[Tulsa World]] |date=February 17, 2016 |url=http://www.tulsaworld.com/scene/movienews/josh-fadem-returns-home-for-tulsans-in-cinema-screening-discussion/article_d292e433-75a4-508e-8de5-6738b08b6fee.html |accessdate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Halperin |first=Moze |title=Staff Picks: Josh Fadem, J Dilla, and Louis CK on 'WTF with Marc Maron' |work=[[Flavorwire]] |date=April 27, 2016 |url=http://flavorwire.com/573620/staff-picks-josh-fadem-j-dilla-and-louis-ck-on-wtf-with-marc-maron |accessdate=June 12, 2016}}</ref>

